docs.abstract: The central bank president oversaw his last monetary policy meeting. Christine Lagarde, his successor, may face a revolt by opponents of his easy-money policies.
docs.snippet: The central bank president oversaw his last monetary policy meeting. Christine Lagarde, his successor, may face a revolt by opponents of his easy-money policies.
docs.lead_paragraph: FRANKFURT — Mario Draghi led his last monetary policy meeting as president of the European Central Bank on Thursday, his legacy as savior of the eurozone clouded by divisions among the bank’s policymakers that have burst into the open in the final months of his tenure.

headline.main: As Mario Draghi Departs, the E.C.B. Is Divided Over His Policies
headline.print_headline: Draghi Departs an E.C.B. Divided Over His Policies
